  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the Living Conditions of Displaced Populations through Site Development and Provision of Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) Services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following the community crisis of June 2019 in the province of Ituri, particularly the territories of Djugu, Mahagi and Irumu, 360,000 people have moved, including 145,400 in spontaneous sites and 214,600 in communities of Home. It is in this context that the present project aims to support the opening of a new site with community infrastructure and roads to accommodate the influx of new internally displaced persons, to relieve existing sites, especially sites of the General Hospital and the ISP and provide Water, Hygiene and Sanitation (WASH) services. This project makes it possible to develop a new site (Lyc&#xE9;e Kigonze), located in the Muzi Maria district, locality of Mudzipela, municipality of Shari, through Site Development, and WASH services.</narrative>
  </description>
